<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-10557] Missing docs when describing topic configs including documentation</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-10557</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When describing topic or broker configs with the AdminClient, we can request the documentation of configuration settings to be included.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This does not work with topic configs. The issue lies in this line:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/kafka/blob/trunk/core/src/main/scala/kafka/server/AdminManager.scala#L767&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/kafka/blob/trunk/core/src/main/scala/kafka/server/AdminManager.scala#L767&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This uses a KafkaConfig object to look up topic configs. Hence for configurations that have different names between KafkaConfig and LogConfig, no documentation is found!&lt;/p&gt;</description>
